on programs that emphasize natural history. This unique patchwork of case-study narratives, philosophical musings, and historical analyses is tied together with commentaries from editors Ian Billick and Mary Price that develop and synthesize common threads. The result is a unique volume rich with all-too-rare insights into how science is actually done, as told by scientists themselves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aEcologyxLongitudinal studiesvCongresses. 0aEcologyxResearchvCongresses. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aAigner, Paul A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlegre, Aylin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAllan, J. David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArmitage, Kenneth B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBillick, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBillick, Ian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCarreño, Geovana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCañizares, Maikel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCurtin, Charles G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCuéllar, Rosa Leny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaza, Félix, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEstes, James A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeinsinger, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFiguera, Mireiza, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlader, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcía, Lainet, econtributor.4ctb4https:/